ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: The event name for which the data was collected

In the last 60 days, did you receive any treatment for your substance use? This includes individual, group, family or couples counseling, medication management, case management, 12-step/self-help group meetings like AA and NA, or any other counseling specifically related to your substance use.
Total number of hours spent participating in substance use treatment sessions over the past 60 days
Notes: Rounded to the Nearest Half Hour

ElementDescription: In the last 60 days, were you scheduled to receive any substance use treatment sessions? This includes individual, group, couples/family therapy counseling, medication management, case management or any other counseling. It does not include educational sessions or 12 step/self help group meetings like AA and NA.
Total number of hours spent participating in substance use treatment sessions over the past 60 days
Notes: Rounded to the Nearest Half Hour

ElementDescription: Comments - tx_services_1
In the last 60 days, did you attend any group therapy/counseling for substance use? Not including 12-step/self-help group meetings like AA and NA
Total number of hours attending group therapy/counseling for substance use over the past 60 days
Notes: Rounded to the Nearest Half Hour

ElementDescription: Comments - tx_services_2
In the last 60 days, did you attend any individual therapy/counseling sessions for substance use?
(If tx_services_3a = 1) Specify type(s) of therapy attended for substance use in the last 60 days
Notes: Motivational Interviewing (MI), Cognitive Behavioral Therapy (CBT), Risk Reduction, Skills Training, Vocation Rehabilitation, medication management, case management,etc.

ElementDescription: Total number of hours spent attending individual therapy/counseling sessions for substance use

Notes: Rounded to the Nearest Half Hour

ElementDescription: Comments - tx_services_5
